GPC DEMO  --  the Greased Piglet Compiler, running natively on the Commander X16
================================================================================

This folder is a HostFS root: point the emulator (or copy it to an SD card) at it and
you get the resident BASIC->P-code compiler plus sample programs to compile and run,
with no PC toolchain involved.

  gpc.prg          the compiler (prompts you for file names)
  gpc.runtime.prg  the little VM the compiler bundles into a standalone build
  HELLO        \
  SQUARES       \  sample programs, as classic tokenized BASIC -- type one of these
  LOGIC          } names at the compiler's "compile file:" prompt. The readable
  INTMATH       /  source for each is in src/<NAME>.bas.
  XKEYS        /
  STRINGS
  c.HELLO      HELLO already compiled -- LOAD"C.HELLO",8 : RUN it right away
  DIR.PRG      a plain-BASIC file lister: LOAD"DIR.PRG",8 : RUN  to see what's on disk

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Run it (emulator)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  x16emu -fsroot demo -prg demo/gpc.prg -run

At the prompts:
  compile file:  SQUARES        (a sample name above)
  write to:                     (just press RETURN -> it auto-names c.SQUARES)

Then, back at the READY prompt, run the compiled program with no compiler present:
  LOAD "C.SQUARES",8
  RUN

Or skip compiling and run the pre-built one immediately:
  LOAD "C.HELLO",8
  RUN

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What each sample shows
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  HELLO    PRINT, FOR/NEXT, strings -- the basics.
  SQUARES  numeric arrays: fill A(I)=I*I in a loop, then read A(I) back by a
           variable subscript in a second loop.
  LOGIC    comparisons and AND / OR / NOT driving IF ... THEN.
  INTMATH  %-suffixed integer variables compile to native 16-bit integer ops
           (integer +, *, and FOR/NEXT) -- markedly faster than ROM float.
  XKEYS    X16-only keywords for free: VPOKE (statement) and VPEEK / HEX$ / BIN$
           (functions) run by handing them to the ROM BASIC interpreter.
  STRINGS  strings live in BASIC's own storage and are reclaimed by the ROM
           garbage collector -- 50 concatenations, then LEN / LEFT$ / CHR$.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Regenerating this folder
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Everything here except this README and src/*.bas is generated. After changing the
compiler, runtime, or a sample, re-stage with:

  scripts/stage-demo.sh

That rebuilds gpc.prg + gpc.runtime.prg, re-tokenizes src/*.bas, and refreshes c.HELLO.
DIR.PRG is a hand-authored utility and is preserved as-is (not regenerated).
